$ Office Object Model: Excel - WorkbookConnection

A `WorkbookConnection` objects stores the information that is required to obtain → development/Data from an *external data source* (that is: not located in the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Workbook[Workbook] itself.

{ Adding a workbook connection with VBA

  gh|about-MS-Office-object-model|/Excel/WorkbookConnection/connections.add2.bas||

  gh|about-MS-Office-object-model|/Excel/WorkbookConnection/img/connections.add2.png||

}

sa:

  The information that is stored in a workbookConnection can also be saved to a *connection file* (with extensions like → development/filename-extensions#odc[`.odc`], `.iqy` etc.) so that they can
  be shared among multiple Excel developers.

  A workbook connection can be used by a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/QueryTable[`queryTable`] object (in which case the query table's property `.workbookConnection` points the respective
  workbook connection.

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model
